Match simulation harness coverage
=================================

The Python tests exercise the deterministic match simulator found under
``tools/tests/match_sim``. In addition to the baseline duel and overtime
scenarios, the suite now bundles ``factory_cvars.json`` to validate the
behaviour of factory-related CVars:

* ``test_factory_loadout_toggle_updates_inventory`` toggles the active
  loadout metadata and ensures bots spawn with the expected ammo and
  inventory stacks, while verifying per-bot overrides remain intact.
* ``test_factory_spawn_delays_emit_client_spawn_events`` checks that
  warmup and live ``ClientSpawn`` events are delayed according to the
  configured factory schedule.
* ``test_factory_item_flags_control_drop_behaviour`` flips the drop and
  bounce flags and compares the resulting item timelines with the golden
  expectations stored in ``tests/expectations/match_sim_factory_items.expect``.

The new scenario is also registered inside ``tests/run_harnesses.py`` so
CI artefact generation captures the extended coverage.

Freeze Tag CVar coverage
------------------------

The ``freeze_cvars.json`` scenario exercises the end-to-end Freeze Tag
flow. ``tests/test_freeze_cvars.py`` drives the harness twice per test so
every ``g_freeze*`` toggle is checked with the relevant observable:

* ``test_spawn_protection_blocks_damage_until_expiry`` verifies the
  damage commands logged by ``shade`` stay blocked until the configured
  protection window expires.
* ``test_auto_thaw_and_inventory_resets`` inspects the recorded
  ``freeze_thaw`` events to ensure the auto-thaw timer fires at 7.5s and
  that the subsequent round reset reapplies the factory loadout, armor
  and powerup stripping.
* ``test_thaw_assist_respects_through_surface_toggle`` compares two
  harness runs (surface blocking enabled and disabled) so thaw assists
  only complete when ``g_freezeThawThroughSurface`` is non-zero.
* ``test_winning_team_credit_thaws_players_when_enabled`` confirms the
  winning team receives thaw credit and that disabling
  ``g_freezeThawWinningTeam`` causes the frozen player to wait for the
  later auto-thaw deadline (~13.2s).

Run the suite with::

    pytest tests/test_freeze_cvars.py -vv

When executing the deterministic harness bundle via ``tests/run_harnesses.py``
the freeze scenario contributes to ``artifacts/tests/logs/<target>/match_sim.log``.
The log lists the scenario slug, seed, and resulting frame count so any
regression immediately stands out in CI artifacts.
